@page "/csv-to-excel"
@inject ProductBranding Branding

<PageTitle>CSV to Excel Converter Online - @Branding.SiteName</PageTitle>
<HeadContent>
    <meta name="description" content="Preview ExcelToolStack CSV to Excel conversion: a public landing page for turning CSV files into structured Excel workbooks with clean columns, review steps, and spreadsheet-ready output." />
    <link rel="canonical" href="@($"{Branding.SiteUrl}/csv-to-excel")" />
    <meta property="og:title" content="@($"CSV to Excel converter online - {Branding.SiteName}")" />
    <meta property="og:description" content="A crawlable preview of a future CSV to Excel tool with static upload UI, conversion workflow, use cases, and FAQ." />
</HeadContent>

<section class="tool-hero converter-hero">
    <div class="tool-hero-copy">
        <p class="eyebrow">CSV to Excel</p>
        <h1>Turn flat CSV data into a cleaner Excel workbook.</h1>
        <p class="lead">
            A public preview of the planned @Branding.SiteName CSV to Excel tool for imports, reports,
            customer lists, exports, and spreadsheet handoffs. This page is static only: no upload,
            conversion, download, or backend processing is connected yet.
        </p>
        <div class="hero-actions">
            <a class="button button--primary" href="/tools">Explore all tools</a>
            <a class="button button--secondary" href="/templates">Browse templates</a>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-proof" aria-label="CSV to Excel tool highlights">
            <span>CSV imports</span>
            <span>Structured workbook preview</span>
            <span>Column review</span>
            <span>Excel-ready workflows</span>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="conversion-panel" aria-label="Static CSV to Excel conversion preview">
        <div class="console-header">
            <span>Conversion workspace</span>
            <strong>Static preview</strong>
        </div>
        <div class="upload-zone" aria-label="Disabled upload area">
            <span class="upload-icon">CSV</span>
            <strong>Drop a CSV file here</strong>
            <p>Upload is intentionally disabled for this landing page.</p>
            <button class="button button--secondary" type="button" disabled>Choose CSV file</button>
        </div>
        <div class="conversion-flow">
            <div>
                <span>1</span>
                <p>Detect columns</p>
            </div>
            <div>
                <span>2</span>
                <p>Preview rows</p>
            </div>
            <div>
                <span>3</span>
                <p>Prepare workbook</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="mock-workbook">
            <div class="mock-row mock-row--head">
                <span>Date</span>
                <span>Customer</span>
                <span>Amount</span>
            </div>
            <div class="mock-row">
                <span>2026-05-01</span>
                <span>Northwind Studio</span>
                <span>$1,240</span>
            </div>
            <div class="mock-row">
                <span>2026-05-03</span>
                <span>Contoso Labs</span>
                <span>$860</span>
            </div>
        </div>
        <p class="disabled-note">
            Frontend shell only. No file is read, uploaded, converted, stored, or downloaded.
        </p>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="section-shell section-shell--tight">
    <div class="section-heading">
        <p class="eyebrow">Use cases</p>
        <h2>Designed for the CSV exports teams keep turning into spreadsheets.</h2>
        <p>
            The future converter is positioned around practical data handoffs, not heavyweight ETL:
            take a simple CSV export and prepare it for everyday workbook review.
        </p>
    </div>
    <div class="workflow-steps">
        <article>
            <span>01</span>
            <h3>Export cleanup</h3>
            <p>Turn CRM, ecommerce, finance, analytics, or operations exports into a workbook your team can inspect.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
            <span>02</span>
            <h3>Column review</h3>
            <p>Preview headers, spot blank fields, review dates and numbers, and prepare clean worksheet structure.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
            <span>03</span>
            <h3>Reporting handoff</h3>
            <p>Move raw CSV data toward spreadsheet reports, templates, formulas, and review workflows.</p>
        </article>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="section-shell section-shell--accent">
    <div class="section-heading section-heading--split">
        <div>
            <p class="eyebrow">Planned workflow</p>
            <h2>A converter shell for cleaner spreadsheet prep.</h2>
            <p>These are planned frontend states only. Conversion behavior can be added later in a separate scoped PR.</p>
        </div>
        <a class="text-link" href="/blog/how-to-generate-excel-formulas-with-ai">Read formula guide</a>
    </div>
    <div class="category-grid">
        <article>
            <span class="category-kicker">Import</span>
            <h3>CSV file intake</h3>
            <p>Future support for selecting a CSV file, detecting delimiter issues, and preparing a worksheet preview.</p>
            <a href="/tools">See all tools</a>
        </article>
        <article>
            <span class="category-kicker">Review</span>
            <h3>Spreadsheet-ready preview</h3>
            <p>Planned review for headers, sample rows, dates, number formatting, blank columns, and row counts.</p>
            <a href="/templates">Pair with templates</a>
        </article>
        <article>
            <span class="category-kicker">Excel</span>
            <h3>Workbook output</h3>
            <p>Future conversion could prepare an Excel workbook for reporting, analysis, formulas, and team handoff.</p>
            <a href="/ai-excel-formula-generator">Preview Formula Copilot</a>
        </article>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="section-shell">
    <div class="section-heading">
        <p class="eyebrow">FAQ</p>
        <h2>CSV to Excel questions.</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-grid">
        <article>
            <h3>Can this page convert CSV files today?</h3>
            <p>No. This is a static public landing page and UI shell. No file processing, uploads, downloads, or backend conversion logic has been added.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
            <h3>Will the future tool create an Excel workbook?</h3>
            <p>The planned positioning is CSV to Excel workbook conversion, with a review step before any future downloadable output.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
            <h3>What CSV files is this page for?</h3>
            <p>It is aimed at common exports from business systems, analytics tools, finance workflows, ecommerce platforms, and internal operations tools.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
            <h3>Is the page crawlable and anonymous?</h3>
            <p>Yes. The route is public, linked from Home and Tools, and listed in the sitemap without auth, billing, or gated behavior.</p>
        </article>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="cta-section">
    <p class="eyebrow">Tool preview</p>
    <h2>Explore CSV to Excel inside the broader spreadsheet workflow shell.</h2>
    <p>
        This page prepares the public surface for a future converter while keeping all behavior static and frontend-only.
    </p>
    <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="button button--primary" href="/tools">Back to Tools</a>
        <a class="button button--secondary" href="/">Return Home</a>
    </div>
</section>
